00ab15d38c9f43678adae873f901a12e
00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:09.440 align:left position:22%
If you could only choose
one chair from this house–

c2bd36eb559b4995becd484bbbab57ed
00:00:09.600 --> 00:00:12.440 align:left position:22%
–which one would it be?

53f4452afc7048faa99f098f1130478a
00:00:13.760 --> 00:00:18.400 align:left position:22%
I'm going to move away from here
to spring next year.

90fb0a04e92f44b4a6eadf19ef40a187
00:00:18.560 --> 00:00:21.960 align:left position:22%
And I can't take them to heaven.

c85dc8af304346bdbe556366a67d71c4
00:00:27.560 --> 00:00:32.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Nordic design has conquered the world
for over a hundred years.</c>

51cf5736f55b40d6b03a2400bd6e8636
00:00:36.360 --> 00:00:37.880 align:left position:22%
I fell instantly.

92e37d76e702499ea3ede2102378877f
00:00:38.040 --> 00:00:41.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>All rooms with this become: Wow!</c>

99f9fb97056344ba9f02d46a0cfb8ad8
00:00:43.720 --> 00:00:45.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But what makes–</c>

52dce9f1e05a44578829537ce4cc9ce4
00:00:45.920 --> 00:00:50.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–Nordic design enchant
collectors from around the world?</c>

6ed2da8a04c84828bbdf9726476a4645
00:00:51.560 --> 00:00:57.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>That wooden sofas and plastic chairs
are sold for fantasy sums internationally?</c>

9e63b699bfff461d9e0b9cf3f6a2ec6b
00:00:57.880 --> 00:01:03.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>From modest everyday objects to
immortal pop culture icons–</c>

3f4abfee45cd466c9946d0246566338e
00:01:03.680 --> 00:01:08.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–seen both on film
and in the world's most exclusive homes.</c>

65d2e79a562e4b2fbd16321240ab5602
00:01:11.840 --> 00:01:17.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>This is a series
about a hundred years of Nordic design–</c>

1bab56fe3e2f469593e3bd3d69a9deef
00:01:17.280 --> 00:01:19.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and why it looks the way it does.</c>

e76cd6483ae14cd9818593be27e890c4
00:01:38.160 --> 00:01:41.680 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Here in the countryside,
in Hokkaido in northern Japan–</c>

7148c494fb364b5b93db32168ea5ac8c
00:01:41.840 --> 00:01:46.440 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–lives the chair collector and furniture researcher
Noritsugu Oda.</c>

56be41271cc04f3cbaa35cfe64776eae
00:01:46.600 --> 00:01:52.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>He has since the 70s been searching for
the optimal closeness to humans–</c>

72d8def2d05d4bc8a6b1aeb0fe3a2f9f
00:01:52.520 --> 00:01:56.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–through searching
for the perfect chair.</c>

a3557554d8e74b8abcea5ff57b5f4a61
00:01:56.680 --> 00:02:03.320 align:left position:22%
Today I have about 1,450 chairs.

d5fbe9959af7494790ba3d261d532ec9
00:02:03.480 --> 00:02:06.280 align:left position:22%
Most are from Scandinavia.

3c489a0c4e0942379373acb9a5954fc5
00:02:06.440 --> 00:02:12.240 align:left position:22%
Objects of high quality
require a certain behavior from people.

f589229d537b4b69accfc2941f7b8a98
00:02:12.400 --> 00:02:18.240 align:left position:22%
You shouldn't sit on a fine chair
in just underwear.

77015f63cc1a4f3780ea37079f336a81
00:02:19.680 --> 00:02:22.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>After a whole life of searching–</c>

b56279a0e51c49bc84a98b7e003141a4
00:02:22.440 --> 00:02:28.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–Mr. Oda has the world's largest
private collection of Nordic chairs.</c>

264010f9f06349928000b71d39b061cd
00:02:28.760 --> 00:02:33.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>His dream is that the furniture one day
will get its own design museum–</c>

2ff8b051cc494ecd84a6ba036268ee27
00:02:34.120 --> 00:02:37.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–showing classic Nordic design.</c>

fb0d00724a6040c386fe8e951610b996
00:02:39.080 --> 00:02:44.880 align:left position:22%
Fast fashion, fast furniture, fast food...

aa37f1910cfe4ab09bd712d50857f0ee
00:02:45.040 --> 00:02:48.080 align:left position:22%
Nowadays everything is fast.

370058b0a66145679b28bc2e8b29b31b
00:02:48.240 --> 00:02:53.960 align:left position:22%
But I have a hundred-year-old furniture
that hasn't lost an ounce of its luster.

d9ee8847e766471bb5a38f36c4fea025
00:02:54.120 --> 00:02:58.000 align:left position:22%
Solid objects possess a quality–

d15b667183244faba919b86137b8207a
00:02:58.160 --> 00:03:03.120 align:left position:22%
–that can influence the world for the better.

ec533739f5c04588b1894df58ed98736
00:03:07.480 --> 00:03:13.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Nordic design is not only loved and coveted
by collectors around the world.</c>

a030152f0914431d9d4c20f7b964133e
00:03:13.880 --> 00:03:16.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It also carries
a winding history–</c>

759cffb3834b49ce82db44bdd0b1a53f
00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:21.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–about the past, present, and the designers.</c>

7dae12e8af614fecbc62d73804a86ec4
00:03:22.720 --> 00:03:27.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>How can a dish rack with boards
become world-famous design?</c>

b01684316f2d4229b5da19f6daf45335
00:03:29.200 --> 00:03:32.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And how does it happen
when an abhorrent pattern–</c>

0f218cbeea5940119d8b8a6ca78f117b
00:03:32.880 --> 00:03:35.640 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–becomes housewives' favorite?</c>

ccdb6232106349d9a2cb955fee8981b5
00:03:36.720 --> 00:03:40.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And how can a small Finnish stool–</c>

45b3ab8851ce4ef086e3568287237d3d
00:03:40.160 --> 00:03:44.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–be part of solving diplomatic
crises during the Cold War?</c>

82f42b86b6b44d049547a7d79a5bdc1d
00:04:12.400 --> 00:04:16.320 align:left position:22%
<c.urfjarran><i>German troops have crossed the border tonight.</i></c>

194d319dbf1e419691d25c572601869c
00:04:16.480 --> 00:04:19.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>A new, big war has broken out.</c>

d7e84a93232440eea2c7a17421b8361b
00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:22.600 align:left position:22%
<c.urfjarran><i>Bombs are falling over Finnish cities.</i></c>

4eb87eec61444838807772da27b34887
00:04:23.320 --> 00:04:26.640 align:left position:22%
<c.urfjarran><i>Fights are taking place</i></c>
<c.urfjarran><i>all the way from the Karelian Isthmus to Petsamo.</i></c>

256355766ab447e98f6bfe1ff9011d5a
00:04:28.600 --> 00:04:31.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>When World War II breaks out–</c>

7e57034b641c40b4a72948af527495b9
00:04:31.240 --> 00:04:35.160 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–the people in the Nordic countries
are affected in different ways.</c>

b130f2ac9676401d9bc4d9a3f944bc77
00:04:35.320 --> 00:04:38.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Finland is involved in three different wars.</c>

9a37a9c637514121a962f9f6e462711a
00:04:38.480 --> 00:04:42.200 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Denmark and Norway
are occupied by Germany.</c>

c54229b5cad14e6c95524b4f64ed3311
00:04:42.360 --> 00:04:48.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Sweden as declared neutral but
several times breaks neutrality–</c>

c5611804affa470bb0fb9e4fb824981d
00:04:48.680 --> 00:04:52.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–escapes being drawn into the war.</c>

b34a712b76964a6fb619e658572c5678
00:04:55.520 --> 00:05:01.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>To make the home warm and cozy with
soft materials and blooming fabrics–</c>

2a6032b72e1f4a459ec40d4a09cef4ff
00:05:02.000 --> 00:05:06.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–is about enduring
the threatening world.</c>

03c47d636e5f4c58868874de66f01529
00:05:12.240 --> 00:05:16.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Estrid Ericson, who runs the interior design store
Svenskt Tenn–</c>

36d8708dc3f146cad0a6f3f2ccca947
00:05:17.040 --> 00:05:22.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–takes the task of making a cold time warm
very seriously.</c>

f46060ba1d6e46afb697d0a11d65d7c7
00:05:22.880 --> 00:05:27.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>As here, in the secretary's apartment
at Millesgården in Stockholm.</c>

629b65ce9f824a35821b927520e92f69
00:05:33.320 --> 00:05:36.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It is nice to live here.</c>

e24cf38415b64c8384725904bbab054d
00:05:37.040 --> 00:05:41.440 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It is messy here.
God, it's so much fun!</c>

da2203391cb64cdab10a8b8da1b185e2
00:05:41.600 --> 00:05:45.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>These
you don't put in the dishwasher.</c>

6464736e49d349e891ce616333161a7c
00:05:46.840 --> 00:05:52.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>When you go to Svenskt Tenn it all feels
perfect, fantastic, and expensive.</c>

fa6941b13ed1405b88b9f488aad7bb73
00:05:52.160 --> 00:05:55.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But when you look at the detail level–</c>

666be8f93a114e698335c164d4cfca60
00:05:55.640 --> 00:06:01.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–you notice that it was something else
that drove Estrid Ericson.</c>

272cebafcc7b4f248356b88e5c01df52
00:06:01.240 --> 00:06:03.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>A wild boar.</c>

55bca32f4a7744ed9d3267df521331aa
00:06:03.200 --> 00:06:08.920 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Here you feel that you don't know
which glass you should be in.</c>

962c6e0c599b4b9093857afb45feb24d
00:06:09.080 --> 00:06:13.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>I would call her beauty addict, which I also am.</c>

1a8b4606bd9748ff875263c9c3ded58a
00:06:15.280 --> 00:06:18.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>A few years before
World War II breaks out–</c>

661d2ba675bc44a1a40b63ae2f126506
00:06:18.680 --> 00:06:23.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–Estrid Ericson hires
the Austrian Josef Frank–</c>

5b75dee7150d4f10ac3200bd2d92357a
00:06:23.280 --> 00:06:26.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–a Jewish architect
who has left his homeland–</c>

80fa2b3b215b4910a3a7ea0bf8237c18
00:06:26.720 --> 00:06:30.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–due to the antisemitic
atmosphere in Vienna's streets.</c>

78e50c852a1941d9a922813c29da054e
00:06:31.040 --> 00:06:36.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>When Ericson and Frank start
collaborating, a kind of music arises.</c>

07ad4bb6d4fd4a61aa10e7c95ed4c83a
00:06:36.880 --> 00:06:41.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>I think Josef Frank understood
what Estrid Ericsson wanted to say.</c>

d5eb6f3fa9164244a997874a1850049b
00:06:41.920 --> 00:06:46.640 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>He understood her melody,
and they found a common language.</c>

c83524b9252f4328b5300756ee329dd1
00:06:52.920 --> 00:06:57.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>His fabrics and furniture
and her ability to decorate–</c>

06814766520d48689f31f7f9e42e4644
00:06:57.760 --> 00:07:04.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–become soft, safe rooms that protect
against the hard reality outside.</c>

85ce87316fa4421cb610e01aa317de32
00:07:04.240 --> 00:07:07.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>When it is toughest
the imagination becomes liveliest.</c>

308567973f9243b48801e792d85a6c9a
00:07:07.960 --> 00:07:10.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>That is why it is so gray,
it must be color.</c>

abf96286808645ffa74f64c8d0ed5270
00:07:11.000 --> 00:07:15.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>They think: "Oh god, it is so gray.
It must be color."</c>

1c69d4fc57c34561866ebcdda941c2de
00:07:17.160 --> 00:07:23.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It was a common understanding that
Estrid Ericsson and Josef Frank had–</c>

0f51e4c011484c24bef5a2d49f037fcf
00:07:23.640 --> 00:07:26.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–to create aesthetic comfort.</c>

f51199ed92524c6ba412eb18594685f1
00:07:33.720 --> 00:07:40.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Ericson and Frank protest
against Swedish squareness–</c>

8a01b4ee65384640854ac51d202c7a4e
00:07:40.160 --> 00:07:46.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and what they mean is a funkis- and
folkhem architecture completely without humor.</c>

fee7ccdeb68f4bf9976cea931f02e9c1
00:07:46.720 --> 00:07:50.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The protest culminates
in a gigantic sofa–</c>

57ad108548cd46ee849afab8464f22b0
00:07:50.920 --> 00:07:54.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–that goes completely against prevailing style ideals.</c>

019ba41c03154d22a9768042244d31da
00:07:54.760 --> 00:07:58.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Josef Frank decides
on a big statement.</c>

2c8925cd08bc4723a8c709d3c1789512
00:07:58.640 --> 00:08:03.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>He shows his huge sofa,
called Liljevalchssoffan.</c>

047bb3326a964f07a6dd01a8b7fa9ddf
00:08:04.040 --> 00:08:07.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>1.40 deep and 2.80 long.</c>

ae43efbb0f104f0d94fb99e91ee58ded
00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:12.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Absolutely not comfortable to sit in,
but wonderful to lie in.</c>

acf607717e284687aadeb2b4108b9fb9
00:08:12.640 --> 00:08:17.200 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It takes SO much space.
He just: "Now I am here!"</c>

4293945e458149579c96be2c8d52b971
00:08:21.600 --> 00:08:24.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Josef Frank
has settled in Sweden–</c>

037aba331b094f15b376eb18de21670f
00:08:25.040 --> 00:08:29.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–but 1941 becomes the development of the war
so alarming–</c>

2d08019023c0459b87c9f13038980c62
00:08:30.120 --> 00:08:35.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–that Josef Frank together with his
wife travels to Manhattan in New York.</c>

65e8bc72ef5f495ba7649d7b40ccc2d0
00:08:38.960 --> 00:08:44.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Josef Frank is again in a new country,
but this time without work.</c>

7b965716a04648b9a98435c5de23515b
00:08:45.120 --> 00:08:51.160 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>To fill the days in exile he begins
to walk on Manhattan's streets–</c>

3f7a5860a3c9443c82737bfee0225340
00:08:51.320 --> 00:08:56.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–which also becomes the beginning
of one of his most beloved patterns.</c>

8001cd40d2e84a6ba7ebbe0ad8ed9290
00:09:01.280 --> 00:09:07.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>He draws up the entire city plan
and all the addresses he likes–</c>

debb6d049bd64bdfa476df5ca10fe788
00:09:07.400 --> 00:09:11.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–so we can follow him on Manhattan,
where he went.</c>

d8a33a43fa8545929d4616b32e6e9adc
00:09:14.160 --> 00:09:17.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Frank draws what he sees
and what he reads about.</c>

90c38cf0dc78490280962e8bdff05768
00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:22.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>He discovers the bold color palette
that exists in Mexico–</c>

1dc53a51fb9b4f52910c40d3f7349f96
00:09:22.160 --> 00:09:25.440 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and mixes it
with his botanical interest.</c>

4f622bb0e51f403aad9246d6e1089e3c
00:09:25.600 --> 00:09:31.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Out comes an entirely own flora
in an exploding color scale.</c>

948e06c1e0a1499c9ef07bdf0eaab93e
00:09:31.760 --> 00:09:35.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>He is funniest when he is
surrealistic and psychedelic.</c>

2a279818936c4684babedf6ea5d221e1
00:09:35.400 --> 00:09:37.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It is a restraint in it–</c>

ccc6df6aaffb47c48dec2882f1e09a61
00:09:38.000 --> 00:09:45.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–but he lets the colors lead the
wilder. It is this ear...</c>

8c7f062e1b154b579c30a4a9d1d920f
00:09:45.880 --> 00:09:52.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>I think Svenskt Tenn is finest
when it is just put together.</c>

ec127903f47c4612b241cd08180f0755
00:09:52.920 --> 00:09:57.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>There becomes a fun meeting
between the different patterns.</c>

4ebba85bbe6a4e108f7c6d38438c879f
00:10:01.320 --> 00:10:06.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The patterns painted in exile he donates
to his friend Estrid Ericson–</c>

bede0b14bf1e4526b9f2d239ed57a107
00:10:06.720 --> 00:10:10.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and they soon become
Svenskt Tenn's signature.</c>

d9760fdf06d84331953e3d8f7ea5cbd4
00:10:10.920 --> 00:10:14.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And when the Swedish pop group ABBA's
music becomes film–</c>

4b72f91264ab41419f1c3b46f71e4fb2
00:10:14.440 --> 00:10:20.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–the Austrian's patterns are used as a
symbol for the most Swedish there is.</c>

59dd03cdf5cf40478497ece4ec9fed3d
00:10:41.760 --> 00:10:48.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Mr. Oda and the Nordic chairs
have been closely intertwined for 50 years.</c>

0518613e0b9f433c9a0cae2594e6e9ad
00:10:48.520 --> 00:10:52.200 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But it was the Swiss modernist Le Corbusier–</c>

f9525602cb6f474d9522b7de0d7cd1d5
00:10:52.360 --> 00:10:57.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–who made Mr. Oda end up
in the chair hell.</c>

5f03a0db406e4458955a8e46952a9b32
00:10:57.520 --> 00:11:02.800 align:left position:22%
At that time
my salary was about 40,000 yen–

ce2a733674be43fa8ad446d63392cc44
00:11:02.960 --> 00:11:07.400 align:left position:22%
–and the Corbusier chair
cost 300,000 yen.

5b165ffbba3f46bb940e3888dc1d7237
00:11:08.800 --> 00:11:14.200 align:left position:22%
So I bought something that cost
seven times more than what I earned–

e0d77e51225048578404f91200146795
00:11:14.360 --> 00:11:17.520 align:left position:22%
–so it became quite tight.

366f8f6dc4254c90a7dd4433f079032f
00:11:17.680 --> 00:11:23.480 align:left position:22%
But when I finally had it
I felt nonetheless very satisfied.

6574da16906a46aa990819a0c9c1a987
00:11:27.120 --> 00:11:31.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The chair LC4
was the gateway for Mr. Oda–</c>

b1665319574d4e11b4343b9a1d330a61
00:11:31.920 --> 00:11:35.680 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–but the obsession
only became bigger and bigger–</c>

60269dc2a5f9498aafdcd8f29492b03d
00:11:35.840 --> 00:11:40.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and eventually the chairs were close
to costing him more than just money.</c>

d0bae2e4ae5d4c6e8a4cf0b1938a8454
00:11:41.680 --> 00:11:46.040 align:left position:22%
For a long time no one understood me.

2f968568a3234984bbaee86b264b3bbb
00:11:46.200 --> 00:11:52.480 align:left position:22%
For half a year I spent a lot of money
on chairs and kept it secret from my wife.

a7a486b15a294ebb9c7d462e0e6de43e
00:11:52.640 --> 00:11:56.840 align:left position:22%
Once I had just spent
a substantial sum–

35af568f960f40829ba6e9a4a48489e7
00:11:57.000 --> 00:12:04.760 align:left position:22%
–and our child
got high fever the same evening.

8c68a3a275d542f9b92582d7188ae886
00:12:04.920 --> 00:12:10.680 align:left position:22%
Fortunately,
there lived a female doctor above us.

a08030276b954a3b90b74b6568344aed
00:12:16.120 --> 00:12:20.880 align:left position:22%
So we took the child to her,
and everything ended well.

e5e4126d01c74bd0af9a907d1171b2f1
00:12:56.800 --> 00:13:04.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Between the years 1939 and 1945
Finland is involved in three different wars.</c>

8ed305af005f457784b5fdf3fc7b5ecb
00:13:04.560 --> 00:13:07.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>This affects everything, even art.</c>

644855d04c42428db4fbd0ec5cd54173
00:13:07.720 --> 00:13:14.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And in the satirical magazine Garm,
the artist Tove Jansson debuts–</c>

4727d06561a042e6bb9847485ee19173
00:13:14.680 --> 00:13:18.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–as political caricaturist.</c>

974c41a3a16a4461b8a3d5e53600661b
00:13:18.520 --> 00:13:23.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Not that I was aware that it was so
remarkable.</c>

f60b76ea03e44ed9bab5474818e9d7f7
00:13:23.880 --> 00:13:29.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>I got assignments to do,
and then I was sometimes...</c>

86e63a2473964b49812c552cde5dbd35
00:13:31.000 --> 00:13:35.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>...so angry at Hitler, and then I made
a picture. It is so simple.</c>

527ec996d9e547c9b746e59306fa84ed
00:13:36.080 --> 00:13:41.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>She draws Hitler as a child
in a tantrum demanding more–</c>

304f820e0f064da5934c3e449e76e044
00:13:41.200 --> 00:13:44.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–despite already having
large pieces of Europe.</c>

0a2e83ad9f124f6da9d040160ce1a764
00:13:44.680 --> 00:13:51.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And it is in Garm that Tove Jansson
first draws this figure.</c>

fab8f1f96ab747f9a5fb2ccabe789050
00:13:51.400 --> 00:13:58.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Then called Snork, but soon
got the name Moomintroll.</c>

95b50282e98040549bf92ace8bdbbc52
00:13:58.640 --> 00:14:01.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It was a small recognition figure–</c>

24263e67a12744e5a9ee5f98a64f1da2
00:14:01.960 --> 00:14:07.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–that ironically foreshadowed and expressed
what was happening in the very image.</c>

6abff805bf6043c684ad8bad12e618cd
00:14:07.880 --> 00:14:12.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Then I took it up
and made it the main character–</c>

741b2b1d5ccc42c1811ad683d8b0a9ac
00:14:13.000 --> 00:14:17.200 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–in all my stories for children.</c>

33c918bcf9ed401fb47723f6117f364f
00:14:17.360 --> 00:14:20.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Then called Moomintroll.</c>

d3789d7410294034acadb3ba14b00038
00:14:29.320 --> 00:14:35.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Tove Jansson's Moomintroll becomes after
the war books, comic albums, and film.</c>

575d1811f735440ba23d05b135cf6a03
00:14:35.440 --> 00:14:38.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But also Finnish design.</c>

7eef3138120c4117b879dd94988d9b3b
00:14:38.400 --> 00:14:42.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Together with the ceramist and glass artist
Kaj Franck–</c>

3647ecd0b98b41ff8cadb877b53655af
00:14:43.000 --> 00:14:48.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–she makes the very first
Moomin tableware in the late 50s.</c>

b30741f6c85140eba370c24564dda272
00:14:53.040 --> 00:14:58.880 align:left position:22%
Have you during your long design career
considered doing something else?

53b6e950467d417e816d1beb81ff3dba
00:14:59.040 --> 00:15:04.680 align:left position:22%
Like this?
Yes, I enjoy it anyway–

7ae9a798ad0a46298a7e85661579ec5e
00:15:04.840 --> 00:15:11.120 align:left position:22%
–because it is something that is
constantly changing and organic.

a71c3dfa6d264fdf8d03eda81553ad1d
00:15:11.280 --> 00:15:16.960 align:left position:22%
In design work you are often
faced with constraints or stress.

dae010628401489a8f7cdcb65ae059f7
00:15:21.200 --> 00:15:26.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>For Kaj Franck's design
the war years play a central role.</c>

5fd8eb6546324b21b2f76288e960c810
00:15:26.240 --> 00:15:29.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>He spends five years
at the coastal artillery.</c>

4cc769d12e7845b8baba12c25b1e4455
00:15:30.120 --> 00:15:36.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>In the harsh everyday life he meets
people from a simpler background–</c>

673c13f5e05a4f20a9f542af99be160b
00:15:37.040 --> 00:15:40.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–which makes him socially aware.</c>

8ba5dd2c98cc4169832da63dca1fa3d3
00:15:45.080 --> 00:15:48.960 align:left position:22%
There were relatively few men there–

eb0c2cc24c274cd5aaef6017e4df2e59
00:15:49.120 --> 00:15:55.880 align:left position:22%
–but he got to learn
and gain understanding of–

78f0740edaa2441b98b6642ff3bcb522
00:15:56.040 --> 00:15:59.800 align:left position:22%
–how they functioned and how they thought.

8108639e78794860bd62c95ce16bcd8c
00:15:59.960 --> 00:16:04.960 align:left position:22%
This affected Kaj's design work
very much.

756fdfb0e2b143948eecdc35e43735b5
00:16:06.600 --> 00:16:10.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Kaj Franck, raised
in a wealthy cultural family–</c>

337a2a6455f74b0dae9382fefaaaf92f
00:16:10.640 --> 00:16:13.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–is used to dinners
on elegant tableware–</c>

4328f943df0245c0b70ec1de84becf85
00:16:13.680 --> 00:16:17.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–but during the war
gets inspired by the peasant society–</c>

b2016023852f4962a8af6d3081bdd4de
00:16:18.040 --> 00:16:22.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and by the allmog objects
that can be used for everything.</c>

1abceee211934423a13d331ca3ae8e55
00:16:23.480 --> 00:16:29.840 align:left position:22%
Kaj used to tell
that one of his guiding stars was the stone bowl–

eda8e6f20fde400e9dfbfd9faa0b5abc
00:16:30.000 --> 00:16:33.920 align:left position:22%
–which was the household's most important object.

c2a2cba566b0497fb1cefbf99991c3f7
00:16:34.080 --> 00:16:40.240 align:left position:22%
It existed in many different sizes
and was used for all possible purposes.

8b88238c46504cbfa63f072b161abbde
00:16:40.400 --> 00:16:44.080 align:left position:22%
You don't need so many things!

f7c1b9aa8a4641609d2207b21de9ba42
00:16:44.240 --> 00:16:48.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>With Kaj Franck the simple allmog bowl
transforms–</c>

0525457b09ce4800b415462f2404ce1b
00:16:48.680 --> 00:16:51.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–into minimalist drinking glasses.</c>

553a37e4d98a422fadc054c6195d58a3
00:16:51.440 --> 00:16:57.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Franck means that the form should be so
functional that the object doesn't notice.</c>

693b33858fb543918644f690883e4d28
00:16:58.000 --> 00:17:01.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Yes, it should be so inconspicuous–</c>

51de238be48d4907abc0fbd8ac9a9f5a
00:17:01.680 --> 00:17:05.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–that the user doesn't ponder
who designed it.</c>

b35b9e7ad5e84838bb15ae205331b0ef
00:17:05.720 --> 00:17:11.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Even more radical he becomes when he
starts at the porcelain company Arabia.</c>

30135d4308ea4ea7907449129b27e799
00:17:12.760 --> 00:17:18.640 align:left position:22%
He saw decoration as unnecessary.
The object should be complete without it.

607965b5da884971989b02042c462de4
00:17:20.000 --> 00:17:25.440 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>"Blow up the tableware!" he says and
rationalizes away handles, spouts–</c>

ed637dc78c564612993925bfb4fa8249
00:17:25.600 --> 00:17:29.920 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and designs lids
that fit several parts.</c>

d9eec3609bfc40d2940b63eaaa097751
00:17:30.080 --> 00:17:33.200 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Color is the only decoration
that is needed–</c>

d4465464153047d2b03a73fc4f344625
00:17:33.360 --> 00:17:39.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and the tableware should be small and
fit in post-war homes.</c>

06828575badb4a18a69b1cfe53fee2da
00:17:40.040 --> 00:17:43.920 align:left position:22%
Everyone should be able to afford them–

0a4802d49a4841c6bfcddba1d9152630
00:17:44.080 --> 00:17:48.600 align:left position:22%
–and they should be stackable
and storable easily.

e5b00a36ce5f4d2dbf0aa6a8393470cb
00:17:48.760 --> 00:17:52.760 align:left position:22%
You shouldn't need a large tableware.

abc28d7627f44929bdd54b7b573eae70
00:17:56.760 --> 00:17:59.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Reasonable, simple, and small.</c>

e79a6ad77df944218cc7d33b94670019
00:17:59.560 --> 00:18:02.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Kaj Franck's ideas were radical then–</c>

3af1d13b055443adbc1f83ea29166422
00:18:02.560 --> 00:18:06.440 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–but self-evident
and highly alive today.</c>

4899b440f78b47d9b19bbd65bc2ea429
00:18:29.960 --> 00:18:36.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>One autumn night 1943 sits
two of the North's foremost designers–</c>

fac06afdb47b42b99882de373336017c
00:18:36.240 --> 00:18:42.680 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–in a leaking rowing boat out on open
sea between Denmark and Sweden.</c>

7021d83002fc4b33aba82eccc1a54a61
00:18:44.440 --> 00:18:50.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>They flee from the occupied Denmark
to escape concentration camps.</c>

015c41665c864686beb84fd0ebba65ba
00:18:51.560 --> 00:18:55.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>One of the designers in the boat
is the satirist, revue maker–</c>

2e057c748f494bebaecfc3af59ca1901
00:18:56.040 --> 00:18:59.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and lamp constructor
Poul Henningsen.</c>

ef61a25b95ab4c0cb77bba834f743e08
00:18:59.760 --> 00:19:05.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>He is known for his lamp shades
that reflect light without blinding.</c>

a6135e06c5b5481d878ceba37c22736c
00:19:06.000 --> 00:19:11.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>He has during the entire 30s conducted
a loud campaign against Nazism–</c>

cb1e018a538b46b786271ae8ddb7d380
00:19:12.000 --> 00:19:15.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–which is the reason
why he now flees.</c>

1350da6f85934e41aaf38531f5e764cb
00:19:16.040 --> 00:19:21.520 align:left position:22%
He wrote criticism and warned publicly
against the Nazification.

26cc673aa43046bf8e695e138de955b8
00:19:21.680 --> 00:19:28.320 align:left position:22%
This provoked the occupying power,
and it was burning under his feet.

9cc621aeb8404d1fb0d4ff5a2d7202f5
00:19:28.480 --> 00:19:34.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>In the escape boat sits also
the star architect Arne Jacobsen–</c>

69a66706e6cf42cd9b34124ed5431c70
00:19:34.200 --> 00:19:38.440 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–who is of Jewish descent,
and his wife Jonna.</c>

785da984896340efb25e547a82e0c227
00:19:38.600 --> 00:19:41.680 align:left position:22%
It was a five-hour journey in the middle of the night–

9d9a9571c0d348168342aebee9e97a57
00:19:41.840 --> 00:19:45.960 align:left position:22%
–from northern Zealand to Landskrona
in a rowing boat.

719979e721a046568dcd069412e6dac0
00:19:46.120 --> 00:19:49.280 align:left position:22%
With two wives bailing incessantly–

23acd3a778974a9bada2651d886f07a3
00:19:49.440 --> 00:19:55.040 align:left position:22%
–and architects who can't row,
in dangerous weather.

fd2910df1d614899b2509e9c100c7a6e
00:19:55.200 --> 00:20:00.840 align:left position:22%
At one point German
patrol boats come and shine over the water.

2bb64e0870af462a8963045dea5d53c8
00:20:01.000 --> 00:20:06.960 align:left position:22%
But they understand that they can't see them
down there in the rowing boat.

2d1b1b81d9e24cd5a05b5aaa81fe507f
00:20:07.120 --> 00:20:12.160 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Arne Jacobsen and his wife Jonna
do not only leave their country.</c>

628fc0047257483db82adc83445b5d57
00:20:12.320 --> 00:20:17.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Jonna also has to leave her two
small children from a previous marriage–</c>

7de14c6b802b4bb2bff1569739c377b9
00:20:17.720 --> 00:20:20.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–with the children's father.</c>

4c9c544c97064976af9d5818fbe6fcda
00:20:20.640 --> 00:20:27.280 align:left position:22%
I know that my mother
was very sad when she was left.

1897a1696fa2425c922c1c63db958857
00:20:27.440 --> 00:20:31.360 align:left position:22%
Mom has now in later years said–

def5696c93ff4ab084a5a98675c9dad8
00:20:31.520 --> 00:20:36.720 align:left position:22%
–that she didn't know they would travel,
that they just suddenly were gone.

f84c74d466dc4c6c8b97beb6ece21c01
00:20:36.880 --> 00:20:44.360 align:left position:22%
It sounds terrible for
an eleven-year-old girl and her little brother.

9e80e91643a945d89ff164ad5dc5b5b1
00:20:46.960 --> 00:20:50.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>7,000 Danish refugees,
mostly Jews–</c>

c00167fefedf4bf9b42c908b295c01a8
00:20:50.440 --> 00:20:55.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–take to the boat over the sound between
Denmark and Sweden in a few months.</c>

6d252eee6cae4b8a8092fc2763ee5ad9
00:20:57.440 --> 00:21:01.200 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Arne Jacobsen and his wife
continue to Stockholm.</c>

5e66ed7d296b427aaae9045d57158348
00:21:03.560 --> 00:21:10.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But for Jacobsen, who introduced
modernist architecture in Denmark–</c>

81f981d1f65044c589b1de26f14fc811
00:21:10.440 --> 00:21:15.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–with the House of the Future and the housing
area Bellavista north of Copenhagen–</c>

b8a149c702de46b284b69663343de102
00:21:15.160 --> 00:21:18.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–the career gets a sudden end.</c>

3443942b38ec411aa59db18f015a761a
00:21:24.720 --> 00:21:31.040 align:left position:22%
He got no commissions on the same level
as he had gotten before the trip.

c39edc0de77246508e0b5e4fb824981d
00:21:31.200 --> 00:21:35.720 align:left position:22%
But grandmother
was educated textile artist–

38dc47a6f42e49349647bf2331d73443
00:21:35.880 --> 00:21:43.400 align:left position:22%
–and had already before the trip exhibited
textiles based on Arne's images.

9298f6f2bfae4383b718ac26a7096d79
00:21:43.560 --> 00:21:46.480 align:left position:22%
And they continued with that up there.

363e6ec14c444a29eb755c05fa163f0
00:21:51.920 --> 00:21:56.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Just like for Josef Frank
the flight from Hitler–</c>

7987d80cf0704204ab79ad8f4d56d549
00:21:56.160 --> 00:22:02.440 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–leads to him searching in himself and
finding a blooming dream landscape.</c>

3bd686a1aa5845ff93aa0977a6db2b23
00:22:03.560 --> 00:22:07.760 align:left position:22%
He was incredibly interested in botany–

1fec4ab4578041a7810f8f046a68a379
00:22:07.920 --> 00:22:11.760 align:left position:22%
–and knew very much about plants.

c798751eaa8c43fcb66dac9d559cd834
00:22:11.920 --> 00:22:19.240 align:left position:22%
And so they made
a sea of fantastic fabrics–

6d1642e4c7b549a59cf501e824370e04
00:22:19.400 --> 00:22:23.240 align:left position:22%
–with plants and flowers.

b74a3e6dde184a94a606027e103400ed
00:22:35.160 --> 00:22:41.840 align:left position:22%
100 years since we got self-determination,
but how much do we determine?

c6961f56f574471ea5fd44239b95463
00:22:42.000 --> 00:22:46.400 align:left position:22%
How many of us
live as we have desire?

2103469080a74659b68b2922470560fe
00:22:46.560 --> 00:22:49.080 align:left position:22%
Desire... Oh dear!

2971deaa87c04ccd8051cc0f5e2d92b7
00:22:49.240 --> 00:22:52.880 align:left position:22%
Then you are natural, and that was just...

5139e28b596e4617b0c4cb92b018b535
00:22:54.360 --> 00:23:01.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>In Stockholm can Poul Henningsen
write satire freely again–</c>

26ce5429835b403787cf9cc054b9e292
00:23:01.400 --> 00:23:07.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–but to make a living he begins
to fold lamps in cardboard.</c>

d946bba65a99441bae596f2f70dfd5b5
00:23:08.000 --> 00:23:11.640 align:left position:22%
He had to settle for what was available.

9af8589b79e04a768ba08cf21c531f32
00:23:11.800 --> 00:23:18.320 align:left position:22%
You find after some effort a little paper,
and it becomes a production–

30e24b50bf4044d9b35542abfb666a9a
00:23:18.480 --> 00:23:23.320 align:left position:22%
–that becomes both ceiling lamps,
pendant lamps, and table lamps.

9acc68e65b3c4d2192d04b7fa73bab9e
00:23:29.320 --> 00:23:32.640 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>When Poul Henningsen
and Arne Jacobsen–</c>

7a28c8a83896495eb2aa06555127f23d
00:23:32.800 --> 00:23:37.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–together with 7,000 other
Jews and outspoken anti-Nazis–</c>

b4b4a12fb7cd43bca4d1648aa5681849
00:23:37.280 --> 00:23:39.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–are in exile in Sweden–</c>

fe9d8c7d4b4148bcad7910fe687c4b7f
00:23:39.880 --> 00:23:44.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–there is a daily life in the homeland
for many others.</c>

9139b95bd5864e1187641de3b349aa27
00:23:44.880 --> 00:23:48.920 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>One of them is the Danish
furniture designer Finn Juhl–</c>

e59230bcb06a46b785e5204ad93bb2d7
00:23:49.080 --> 00:23:56.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–who creates unpredictable forms
inspired by nature and art.</c>

f7333b9acb6042e6aa53333e9d12f303
00:23:56.160 --> 00:23:59.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>His furniture he sees as sculptures.</c>

68702a998a3a4e7eb3dbd33f35a3c94a
00:23:59.920 --> 00:24:06.920 align:left position:22%
Finn Juhl makes slender constructions
that are simultaneously organic forms.

b0fc8b3d5fa9418baa2aab0c70d81c6a
00:24:07.080 --> 00:24:13.240 align:left position:22%
He is inspired by Egyptian furniture art
and wants to bring out the animal-like in furniture.

8efc30c86af7417b9730c9733b3c7aca
00:24:13.400 --> 00:24:19.680 align:left position:22%
He translates the rather cold
Central European modernism–

57712080898b43bcb1c75d81c9218327
00:24:19.840 --> 00:24:25.240 align:left position:22%
–to something more human
with animal-like, flowing forms.

eb26c639f5e81440b1b5e5efdaf65e21
00:24:37.760 --> 00:24:42.440 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>In Denmark Finn Juhl is called
"building deaf" by critics–</c>

8468f3223a3e4b01bd597ddbfa3bd514
00:24:42.600 --> 00:24:46.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and the prominent designer
Børge Mogensen–</c>

3f4810c5611e4a94901cf7084f308703
00:24:46.440 --> 00:24:50.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–accuses Finn Juhl
of mixing cocktail furniture–</c>

d3d75c2b405b4367ac607377d40377cb
00:24:50.560 --> 00:24:54.920 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–instead of creating function
for ordinary people–</c>

03db4b880b9e4322b71498a3a0043527
00:24:55.080 --> 00:25:00.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–something that was Børge Mogensen's
own motto in his design.</c>

74de0161d5834d028699b3958647baf8
00:25:01.040 --> 00:25:04.200 align:left position:22%
People laughed at Finn Juhl in the beginning–

d9facb9b6d29459383a9722503c43eaa
00:25:04.360 --> 00:25:11.360 align:left position:22%
–because his furniture is so sculptural,
almost no longer furniture.

fc38736587174cafa91703dd7824748d
00:25:15.840 --> 00:25:22.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But as ridiculed as Juhl becomes in
Denmark, as loved he becomes in the USA.</c>

4caab3f245a34dde8945b8bd3cc328e3
00:25:23.000 --> 00:25:29.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>He furnishes the UN headquarters
in New York and Denmark's embassy.</c>

ee168a4c88f44c9a9f4684d06f550bfd
00:25:29.720 --> 00:25:34.640 align:left position:22%
He doesn't make furniture
for workers' two-room apartments–

03d7a0826ad8464ab8d317b6c89ccd53
00:25:34.800 --> 00:25:37.920 align:left position:22%
–but he makes art. Which provokes.

99ecf61202d447caa84ba7eb57a7eb3a
00:25:39.800 --> 00:25:45.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Juhl lays the foundation for the Danish
modernism's breakthrough in the world–</c>

9b291bb0fa2248cb9462e597e88addf6
00:25:45.560 --> 00:25:50.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–but the designer's success story
gets a sudden end.</c>

f3085b337e9940e39c7bbd97fd586c6c
00:25:51.600 --> 00:25:56.560 align:left position:22%
Finn Juhl is one of the greatest
in the 50s and 60s.

c33c3a3a1ece4a3f913d91ffd2952e05
00:25:56.720 --> 00:26:03.000 align:left position:22%
His furniture is manufactured in the USA, but then
the world changes and we get pop culture.

a9d1c5f800a3411b8ccdc300ac08cd02
00:26:03.160 --> 00:26:10.560 align:left position:22%
Plastic furniture and synthetic
materials come, and then it goes downhill for Juhl.

903894129f7540a29ba71ad96c32d6ab
00:26:10.720 --> 00:26:13.960 align:left position:22%
No one is interested in his furniture.

c1f6d7dfe4574685bd28402e94b8e7ad
00:26:20.720 --> 00:26:27.200 align:left position:22%
I wanted to interview Finn, but a Japanese
who was knowledgeable about Denmark claimed–

8b9e532caaa7485aa41f70e5d1af70c0
00:26:27.360 --> 00:26:33.360 align:left position:22%
–that he had severe alcohol problems
and was largely forgotten in Denmark.

15864d7e14ca43249b8c2b184b158b7b
00:26:33.520 --> 00:26:39.880 align:left position:22%
So everything I heard was negative,
but I wrote to ask for a meeting–

4265b4bd50cc494dbe58147dbc4480a0
00:26:40.040 --> 00:26:44.400 align:left position:22%
–and when I went there
I was warmly received.

209ef1d69f2d4db4b30998832456afd6
00:26:44.560 --> 00:26:48.560 align:left position:22%
After that we kept in contact for six years.

c17640661c9b44518968e8bd7a153352
00:26:49.440 --> 00:26:57.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The friendship between Mr. Oda and Juhl
lasts until Juhl's death in 1989.</c>

ec0b994132414005ad36d4358f6f7dd6
00:26:57.280 --> 00:27:01.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Then Mr. Oda has had exhibitions
with Juhl's furniture in Japan–</c>

bbeb94f9c5d746b5be8714d87df35d1d
00:27:02.120 --> 00:27:05.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and slowly but surely
the Danes begin to look–</c>

c080502214fc444cad19662d7d2c76c6
00:27:05.400 --> 00:27:11.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–at their eccentric and possibly
building deaf designer with love again.</c>

d759ef46b0874da9b0e91d8a97c2ae37
00:27:24.080 --> 00:27:27.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>When Germany occupies Norway
during World War II–</c>

4723830d61314cddb5884b1b52edc741
00:27:27.640 --> 00:27:31.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–they are met by both a military
and a civilian resistance.</c>

2691c1d4c3c34609ade72c315fbe3d02
00:27:31.400 --> 00:27:37.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But the resistance lives dangerously,
and eventually many have to flee.</c>

9f45f3f3fcb74fab950544ae94249596
00:27:37.480 --> 00:27:42.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>One of them is the Norwegian goldsmith
Grete Prytz Kittelsen.</c>

dff4493c8a824679a7d91fef1d598cf7
00:27:45.000 --> 00:27:50.520 align:left position:22%
As so many others
was Grete active in the resistance–

cb5ef1f5bd804c6c873de344949e5870
00:27:50.680 --> 00:27:57.200 align:left position:22%
–and there came a point
when she could no longer be in Norway–

4601c06beb774bc1ad8262cd89236a3f
00:27:57.360 --> 00:28:01.720 align:left position:22%
–so she fled on skis over the border–

45236a4e2c8f458b9c8262cd89236a3f
00:28:01.880 --> 00:28:05.360 align:left position:22%
–and settled in Sweden.

7cdae4bf5d614e87860abb01ce83f3b6
00:28:05.520 --> 00:28:11.680 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The goldsmith Grete Prytz Kittelsen
is one of nearly 50,000 Norwegians–</c>

cac4702b91754aeb9bb512d6ea0fbb80
00:28:11.840 --> 00:28:14.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–who have to flee to Sweden.</c>

b9ac61aecf5a4bb88efda4ba07ef30c1
00:28:14.920 --> 00:28:19.960 align:left position:22%
In Stockholm it was
very many Norwegians who socialized.

e560dd32122947a48ac5cff8ff80df68
00:28:20.120 --> 00:28:27.480 align:left position:22%
And one of them she had had
as a teacher, the architect Arne Korsmo–

258c0ab7ea9e4c91bdd9a3b4658a8eb4
00:28:27.640 --> 00:28:31.440 align:left position:22%
–got she such a good contact with–

04c76fa33e9c4ed7a9cca40666185c0e
00:28:31.600 --> 00:28:36.880 align:left position:22%
–that they married under a lunch break
on the embassy in Stockholm.

b4df7ee476284b4e8657f543a249b2bb
00:28:42.880 --> 00:28:49.160 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>After the war they return to Norway
and become their most powerful design couple.</c>

80772d19ac894dc39d8270a9157655fc
00:28:49.320 --> 00:28:54.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Here they design and build a house that
is both their home and workplace.</c>

1ef4d87021944c5cb5ccf5693cd71573
00:28:55.800 --> 00:29:01.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The house on Planetveien 12 in Oslo
becomes modern architecture history.</c>

b8caec1526d04fc0995425408c1fb537
00:29:06.760 --> 00:29:12.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Together and separately they design
cutlery, plates, vases, and bowls–</c>

c83e41da62344d9ca38f19a3070f3a7c
00:29:13.120 --> 00:29:16.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–for the post-war modern home.</c>

70397658a5224935b7b894f99ff644da
00:29:16.960 --> 00:29:22.320 align:left position:22%
It was a time marked
by reconstruction after the war.

83a22f58691e41ebaf2fd6e5886e156b
00:29:22.480 --> 00:29:28.680 align:left position:22%
There were many who needed
new things for their homes:

e93f336875e14865b6bb22a43c240dd0
00:29:28.840 --> 00:29:35.080 align:left position:22%
Plates, plates and bowls. And people
wanted to go out and party and have jewelry.

89da8c6765b148a94ed41f22e857099
00:29:35.240 --> 00:29:39.840 align:left position:22%
It was a good time
for Norwegian product designers.

97222b4fd15e4591bed4893c738fe3ec
00:29:41.280 --> 00:29:46.400 align:left position:22%
Here is an example in enamel,
a very popular ashtray–

d80fcbb897724569b10a2e4660426f40
00:29:46.560 --> 00:29:51.040 align:left position:22%
–that among others was delivered
to the White House.

4e49cc5a647b451186db05afc2f268fd
00:29:53.200 --> 00:29:56.400 align:left position:22%
I like clean, clear colors–

ffb3f75843f74f36b918b1658136475e
00:29:56.560 --> 00:30:01.000 align:left position:22%
–and when working
with transparent enamel on silver...

8696557caee5432fbdf2f5776bb180d3
00:30:01.160 --> 00:30:07.640 align:left position:22%
What has been important for me
is that I make a whole of it.

d95f7c73e6044a558b7fccef9c17fad9
00:30:07.800 --> 00:30:14.160 align:left position:22%
I work with the silver, so that it gives
light and shadow and shines through.

cf3eba1f35274576bd4ded1ea2ce99ba
00:30:16.320 --> 00:30:22.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Grete Prytz Kittelsen becomes
"the queen of Scandinavian design".</c>

21e73321065b4016912348850df856b4
00:30:22.440 --> 00:30:28.920 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But it is an abhorrent pattern
designed by Arne Ingemann Clausen–</c>

9ee52496a2c14f67a9b1497abe661f61
00:30:29.080 --> 00:30:33.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–that makes her
"the people's designer".</c>

5f9f33aae4784a8bad164398a8350877
00:30:34.400 --> 00:30:38.800 align:left position:22%
Grete wanted gladly
that if there should be pattern–

e4aee71dced147f8898b52f0771d1de5
00:30:38.960 --> 00:30:44.680 align:left position:22%
–so it should be engraved in the metal
and fit beautifully with the form.

5727fa0f1a984e63948155ee6063df63
00:30:44.840 --> 00:30:51.880 align:left position:22%
Then it was produced in Cathrineholm's
factory in Halden at the Swedish border.

628990dc6cb040689c933e8d68020c5b
00:30:52.040 --> 00:30:56.680 align:left position:22%
They had a panel housewives
who should choose patterns.

a40f1e9871f7432b8dc2b873c8f3c8b8
00:30:56.840 --> 00:31:03.600 align:left position:22%
One of the patterns Grete had not made,
but the housewives preferred–

688034d2ef9b44ffaaf60e10c62ac671
00:31:03.760 --> 00:31:09.760 align:left position:22%
–a lotus pattern Grete did not like.
She did not like such decoration.

68d15c1f50d84526aacc38a376b5ff14
00:31:09.920 --> 00:31:14.040 align:left position:22%
But it was produced and became a hit.

39f345c968ad4bb2a5dda55deda8d8ee
00:31:15.000 --> 00:31:18.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Grete Prytz Kittelsen's
pots, plates and coffee pots–</c>

95cbf75fc22044d98da9f4768fc2c43d
00:31:19.040 --> 00:31:22.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–are mass produced
at the Cathrineholm factory–</c>

a924564996884dab85b8aac01f9222c8
00:31:23.000 --> 00:31:28.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–but to her great disappointment,
with the abhorrent pattern on.</c>

07e450a77ec049238cd79abbbeda8470
00:31:28.400 --> 00:31:34.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And when the TV series Mad Men recreates
the 60s, the Lotus bowls are brought out.</c>

e4260f5b4655444db78595cca6c861a8
00:31:51.360 --> 00:31:54.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>If Grete Prytz Kittelsen
is "the people's designer"–</c>

6cdb212194264791a7be38b4b8069add
00:31:55.120 --> 00:31:59.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–it is completely the opposite for the young
carpenter Bruno Mathsson.</c>

6d04fedfdf37467ba0417557b0fe0aaf
00:31:59.520 --> 00:32:04.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>He shakes up all of Sweden.
Yes, actually large parts of the world–</c>

7e1b517c66324518bcc3d8a00c0639f3
00:32:04.960 --> 00:32:08.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–when in the beginning
of the economically pressed 30s–</c>

daa0936ac63d444ea3caf180ece3e9fc
00:32:08.200 --> 00:32:12.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–he does something so drastic
as to undress a chair.</c>

3b3ef8fb65f542fdbf28a7c1321c581c
00:32:21.360 --> 00:32:25.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>In seating furniture they had
a lot of stuffing and springs.</c>

d5ff2a82711d4aaca805f9bd3a185397
00:32:26.040 --> 00:32:30.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Cost-wise it became
also at that time too expensive–</c>

ecc1fd45bd364e689076b0dbeb8e8778
00:32:30.680 --> 00:32:36.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–so I undressed a chair down to
the bottom and came down to saddle straps.</c>

a0090002f9564b0a993bad3417e6eb46
00:32:37.880 --> 00:32:40.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Saddle straps you have had for a long time.</c>

4e2813d76e9e4cb99372df4d36a0ccbc
00:32:40.960 --> 00:32:44.440 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>On 1700s chairs
it is a saddle strap underneath–</c>

3bfc291e9f0c488da677769b994dd4bc
00:32:44.600 --> 00:32:49.920 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–then a stuffing of tow or something
and then comes the actual fabric.</c>

f81125310f214bd8ba3c1ab2513366cc
00:32:50.080 --> 00:32:56.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>To leave it raw with the construction
visible was very innovative.</c>

4e2813d76e9e4cb99372df4d36a0ccbc
00:32:56.960 --> 00:33:01.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>For the general public
you must have been ahead of your time.</c>

d93b84b0adac4415bc2639dcb18e938b
00:33:01.560 --> 00:33:04.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Yes, I am probably still–</c>

fad9ffdf9b3246e598535ada1ff31185
00:33:04.640 --> 00:33:11.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–so it is probably more extreme people
and esthetes who have embraced the ideas.</c>

dfb3b86b5ff84455b70ec66850686760
00:33:14.360 --> 00:33:16.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Innovative and economical.</c>

e91319c1d59a474989eed47b877c88e0
00:33:17.120 --> 00:33:23.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Mathsson gets down the price considerably by
removing the expensive stuffing.</c>

4bac3c8089c5404683bdc6517dcc8e51
00:33:23.680 --> 00:33:28.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But the undressed chair, which is
ordered for Värnamo hospital–</c>

d72a6158350b4c8d9580c882a73fc588
00:33:28.400 --> 00:33:33.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–is too radical and too rational
for the staff at the hospital.</c>

e7ab5467a9904785b77f244d0114fc8e
00:33:36.200 --> 00:33:40.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>They called it the Grasshopper
at the hospital–</c>

5223390d87974e4eb8caa267fd3b9437
00:33:40.920 --> 00:33:47.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and the nurses thought it was
so ugly that they put it in the attic.</c>

050baccbe3434747b6e0c5421b7d959a
00:33:47.760 --> 00:33:51.920 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>No, the experiment with the Grasshopper
became a fiasco–</c>

28e733d365b545ef85e0c895baf244d3
00:33:52.080 --> 00:33:59.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–but Bruno Mathsson is only occupied
with one thing, the mechanics of sitting.</c>

eb6698f1034440daa7124f2021262c0b
00:33:59.560 --> 00:34:03.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>By purifying the sitting curve–</c>

5d52945ebb4f46b9ac09d4971371b6f7
00:34:03.240 --> 00:34:07.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–I could build with saddle straps
as the bearing material.</c>

8b824115176d471fb82a6a2c2ff27f2d
00:34:07.280 --> 00:34:11.160 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But to get variation in this–</c>

c42c42c416a54bcf97636ab636fb1e60
00:34:11.320 --> 00:34:15.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–I dressed it up again
with different fabrics.</c>

31a5bb5360784875942c14519746df8e
00:34:15.720 --> 00:34:20.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It is told that he goes out in
the winter and sets himself in a snowdrift–</c>

1b012f798c5849d19ee349d87e5ca10f
00:34:20.480 --> 00:34:23.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and then measures up the curve
of his own body–</c>

d53ed6b443c54e0ca35f7805f9d1d72f
00:34:23.880 --> 00:34:28.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–to find
the right ergonomic form for the back.</c>

2b9aa4f344094d538a23b425b9ac3cb9
00:34:28.560 --> 00:34:32.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>This he then uses
in his various bentwood forms–</c>

ac585e39e6e94ae08fd1e997c964e522
00:34:33.000 --> 00:34:36.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–to have perfect support for the back.</c>

f1ea5f34fc064b0caee9860cd9f18f7a
00:34:40.040 --> 00:34:43.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Bent laminated wood
is a modern technique–</c>

d075a5e654b043faab39f699b7ab0e0a
00:34:43.680 --> 00:34:47.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–which among others the designer
Alvar Aalto uses.</c>

560c1f3ad0b344359af4bf1cefc17cbc
00:34:47.720 --> 00:34:53.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Bruno Mathsson takes over the method
for his chairs to also sag.</c>

a9e88f53d5f04e398062796bf5e5b72b
00:34:53.880 --> 00:34:59.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>I always tried to make chairs so
one gets a more relaxed way of life–</c>

aab09d8e127f4609ab2434d1e640ba6e
00:34:59.480 --> 00:35:05.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and can relax from hard work,
to get rest in other words.</c>

839770fbade4452da7c238b76e21a80a
00:35:10.720 --> 00:35:15.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And the chair at Värnamo hospital
got vindication with time.</c>

b670285492104667a627983ad4d6aedb
00:35:16.600 --> 00:35:20.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>When I later broke through,
they changed their minds–</c>

b397815d683f46a1ae075b7011361bae
00:35:20.480 --> 00:35:24.920 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and took it down again
and thought it wasn't so bad.</c>

bd273af68dfd44aca51e45c64e4751c4
00:36:13.320 --> 00:36:18.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The war in which Finland
has been involved is now over.</c>

69d822d7b2aa4e0b8f5f96b1e3fefae4
00:36:18.880 --> 00:36:22.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The civilian population
has with admirable courage–</c>

3cf3591f038147c88a0b5e93c24916b0
00:36:22.160 --> 00:36:26.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–resisted terror
of daily air bombardments.</c>

fa2843e755de4e5c9d106addbd1e7bf4
00:36:29.200 --> 00:36:33.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>When the war ends, Finland stands
on the losing side–</c>

c058b19616964853ac2b4601bd2c9e37
00:36:34.000 --> 00:36:39.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–but retains its independence,
and a time of reconstruction follows.</c>

7d2e638ba4034165876ef75ec8043ab5
00:36:40.000 --> 00:36:44.160 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It is now
that a small Finnish stool is designed–</c>

398f9e76770c43abb28a47c206e3c31d
00:36:44.320 --> 00:36:49.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–that is part of solving the future's
diplomatic crises.</c>

e39ce75a04864c48a18696cdd5229fd6
00:36:52.280 --> 00:36:57.400 align:left position:22%
–What are they building there?
–Helsinki's newest hotel.

d52075c316104ef08e5881c7cd8d48d8
00:36:57.560 --> 00:37:01.080 align:left position:22%
There the games' official visitors will stay.

62d665ae60e7461f9abdf25251f9e085
00:37:02.800 --> 00:37:09.320 align:left position:22%
The construction project was grand and should
be seen as a unified art work.

04dd3396683546ecabd996ff8ee460a0
00:37:09.480 --> 00:37:17.120 align:left position:22%
In addition to the architecture,
all interior was designed solely for that building.

9b340f83817c447698b3937c561dbae2
00:37:18.880 --> 00:37:23.640 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>To the hotel's sauna,
the heart of the modernist dream–</c>

9ac9005504d349d0b6c839f85716fe08
00:37:23.800 --> 00:37:29.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–designs Antti Nurmesniemi
a horseshoe-shaped sauna bench.</c>

721b68f86f794931b186eea125601d8f
00:37:29.760 --> 00:37:36.240 align:left position:22%
The building was very modern and
represented the new modernism–

a4503f7a6e7648488645ff9762fb469f
00:37:36.400 --> 00:37:40.760 align:left position:22%
–while the bench was the traditional
in new guise.

04030e3875bc41b0bc7ab4951fcbb2a7
00:37:42.040 --> 00:37:47.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The bench with hole in the middle and sloping
sides so that the water runs down–</c>

d1dd9bd620e049009d0476249d5cd096
00:37:47.920 --> 00:37:53.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–will play a central role
in the Finnish sauna diplomacy–</c>

402e99d0e9644d67ad46c5f042a84af8
00:37:53.200 --> 00:37:58.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–when Finland's president
has important political meetings in the sauna.</c>

397e1e634c604507a1b5e5efdaf65e21
00:37:59.520 --> 00:38:04.720 align:left position:22%
Sauna diplomacy meant that Kekkonen
invited Finnish politicians to the sauna.

139b4ff9067844b08615ebceca978229
00:38:04.880 --> 00:38:10.800 align:left position:22%
Issues were discussed in a relaxed
environment – the sauna is relaxing after all.

b91b37264a244d028a624466e0085ca3
00:38:10.960 --> 00:38:15.760 align:left position:22%
It becomes easier to make decisions
in a pleasant atmosphere.

eb43773988754ea08973cdabd1610cb5
00:38:21.920 --> 00:38:28.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>During the Cold War continues Finnish
politicians their conversations in the sauna–</c>

a3c5c0a93b7c4b22b9550d722cc5a0df
00:38:28.200 --> 00:38:31.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–but now with Soviet leaders.</c>

5046674a4e67486fb8232ac1e7a564b1
00:38:31.480 --> 00:38:36.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The stable sauna bench was created
for the peaceful world–</c>

2dcde75293fc4cfb8485047576c4ef83
00:38:36.400 --> 00:38:39.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–but gets instead to bear heavy loads–</c>

961f145c27174784ae551edfa78df1bb
00:38:39.400 --> 00:38:43.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–when naked world leaders
have hot discussions on it.</c>

e479ac773cb24df0a18696cdd5229fd6
00:38:44.040 --> 00:38:47.200 align:left position:22%
Sauna diplomacy has lived on.

025eb020fc304485904aa2efd90f2336
00:38:47.360 --> 00:38:52.960 align:left position:22%
Finland's embassies abroad
have used their saunas–

40b00f3013a2488b831c143af4756b7f
00:38:53.120 --> 00:38:56.160 align:left position:22%
–as meeting places for diplomats.

22061566c14f4798932c91a58879c65b
00:39:20.880 --> 00:39:26.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>In step with people moving
from countryside to cities–</c>

a1914bff08d34283ae8b44a5c23027d5
00:39:26.560 --> 00:39:30.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–many of the middle class women become housewives.</c>

32b2fbf754804ea4a3fb6f0a9d6d5dc3
00:39:30.520 --> 00:39:35.160 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Studies are made
to streamline the kitchen work–</c>

89a134610cd14607959176ae4c1e623d
00:39:35.320 --> 00:39:38.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and the designers
Nils and Kajsa Strinning invent–</c>

7f78dd193e15489abc78171885d292f8
00:39:39.040 --> 00:39:43.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–both a wastebasket
and a revolutionary dish rack–</c>

ad67cba5beb4412193605a8fceffc805
00:39:43.400 --> 00:39:46.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–to relieve
the poor housewife.</c>

6ec55a9d7db94df99873a0261e087bad
00:39:52.640 --> 00:39:57.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>I can go into a kitchen
in Switzerland or Germany–</c>

2bd108970c204f97b44787dfad5f2130
00:39:57.560 --> 00:40:03.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and if I have something to throw away
and open a hatch in the sink–</c>

1c42d2be5dba4772af2cdcac80391feb
00:40:03.520 --> 00:40:05.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–then there sits one of those.</c>

6ceb95ed67194174a91c16f62c344d4e
00:40:07.320 --> 00:40:12.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Nils and Kajsa Strinning are popular
in radical housewife circles–</c>

b76c1ff924be466994018cf78aec37c5
00:40:12.480 --> 00:40:17.920 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–just because they see the invisible
work that housewives do.</c>

b45bd51ac6904096960e033c85a96cdf
00:40:18.080 --> 00:40:21.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>They continue
to experiment with the dish rack–</c>

9adf952078ec4b6f98f66fee6611197a
00:40:21.400 --> 00:40:28.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and one day Nils lays boards
on the plastic-coated steel wire rods.</c>

18c36fa04a104238a44ffeffacea0829
00:40:30.200 --> 00:40:37.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>I rushed out to my wife
and drew up the little ladder.</c>

158c26b1a0354afe921c42679e37e81d
00:40:38.000 --> 00:40:44.680 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>She pushed it aside and said
that we had so much other to do.</c>

a6c5a9848b6743ff930ddd968ab036f3
00:40:44.840 --> 00:40:51.440 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But when I get rejected by her
can it be something really good on the way.</c>

1ffeda27b904442898b4d763adb74c95
00:40:56.960 --> 00:41:00.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>What Kajsa says is this:</c>

37c8e8af8dc345a59141080eb4342750
00:41:00.960 --> 00:41:08.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>"Often she saw to that the ideas
were refined and documented."</c>

b4ef24e77faf48f7b169773a5f641ffd
00:41:08.280 --> 00:41:10.680 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It sounds like everything.</c>

381d01d569274d839baf1403cf7f8eac
00:41:10.840 --> 00:41:16.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>What is it in this thing
that makes it so interesting?</c>

b5a9b98c13f14de784275214adbc71a7
00:41:16.960 --> 00:41:20.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Well, call it...</c>

86e15fe1007e49779d681be10c52538e
00:41:20.280 --> 00:41:23.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>"Elegance" perhaps is a good expression.</c>

8ea479946cdf4ec9a6f0caa35125ed6d
00:41:24.600 --> 00:41:31.440 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Well, perhaps it is the elegance that makes
the String shelf into a classic–</c>

5a942774bb5146c3bd55cc9773f0d2e4
00:41:31.600 --> 00:41:35.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and has written Kajsa
and Nils Strinning into design history.</c>

6f594171f25d4198aa4135bd45dbb7b5
00:41:38.280 --> 00:41:42.960 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>For surely it is so that we all
want to be remembered for something?</c>

caf99f1cd50542ca8c418848dc638827
00:41:43.120 --> 00:41:48.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>In Norway is the designer Bendt Winge
known for this stackable chair–</c>

371c75b4efa84cad9c2f3f15d8f70171
00:41:48.760 --> 00:41:52.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–that has been sold
in more than seven million copies.</c>

bb89f022bb9244c1bd89dadf3bd6225e
00:41:52.880 --> 00:41:59.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>But his real masterpiece,
the chair Condor, designed 1959–</c>

fa34bfe4ba6445b4bf607adea3c7ce38
00:42:00.040 --> 00:42:06.120 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–was manufactured only in a few
copies that disappeared and were forgotten.</c>

a383aee7904e4a0cbc619f88a46a1d0
00:42:06.280 --> 00:42:11.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Today exists the only
remaining copy here in Japan.</c>

f7d1020666894cae9ba704f0e3fe5024
00:42:14.680 --> 00:42:19.080 align:left position:22%
This is
Bendt Winges chair with high back.

bb809d38c3cc46eea8927bfd37a4ff42
00:42:19.240 --> 00:42:23.840 align:left position:22%
In Denmark there was
a design magazine called Mobilia–

2ec4e6c6ff104e709bbe4753d4742453
00:42:24.000 --> 00:42:27.640 align:left position:22%
–and it had a full page with the chair.

9018d7ec5a5243c993109d234d586664
00:42:27.800 --> 00:42:32.200 align:left position:22%
So it was surprising
to see it in a shop in Daikanyama.

aac1f16068ad4b0fb40fd66634336d0d
00:42:32.360 --> 00:42:37.280 align:left position:22%
I thought
that it should be preserved for posterity.

f8e69aa260054a46b9a8c7286ced0d06
00:42:39.400 --> 00:42:46.800 align:left position:22%
This set is probably the only
copy that exists in the world.

97bc8521bacc467bb1c9387d0b5af96c
00:42:47.760 --> 00:42:53.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The chair that almost disappeared
stands now safely with Mr. Oda–</c>

428dd6438c90496d832a3042dcfd9811
00:42:53.400 --> 00:42:58.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and perhaps that will make Bendt Winge
now be remembered–</c>

1e088dc2e178430c80c372a42c1d1244
00:42:58.520 --> 00:43:03.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–for the chair that he considered
his artistic pinnacle.</c>

e0bd477bfaea4c25b6263425177b5135
00:43:05.120 --> 00:43:11.680 align:left position:22%
If you could only choose
one chair from this house–

b7ba2ee13c7e462796566ef6a2b6d5c5
00:43:11.840 --> 00:43:15.200 align:left position:22%
–which one would it be?

b7c9befdb2ab4ce697820c2983097e71
00:43:16.960 --> 00:43:21.640 align:left position:22%
Well, then it would be this one.
It is small also.

4ed4b90ba0174713af5e680cdeb66532
00:43:21.800 --> 00:43:24.920 align:left position:22%
I don't need larger things anymore.

99fdc951926943a19dc5b0abcebdbd16
00:43:29.480 --> 00:43:32.200 align:left position:22%
This is...

5c0da1b3d58b4e2d9e7b15134355d890
00:43:32.360 --> 00:43:35.360 align:left position:22%
Hans Wegner.

27d1e70246c84a89a3ed92dd7ba8e8b6
00:43:41.560 --> 00:43:47.160 align:left position:22%
A chair is something you can sit on,
and should be made as simple as possible.

277baf816ebd4660b86991218b2aa950
00:43:47.320 --> 00:43:53.040 align:left position:22%
And that it gets the expression I have myself,
cannot be helped.

1f22313785894cc482552613c4e3527d1
00:43:53.200 --> 00:43:56.880 align:left position:22%
I don't know why they look like they do.
They just do.

3e44542274c84f92ba90a71f1f3dbeb2
00:43:58.960 --> 00:44:04.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Hans Wegner creates during his lifetime
around 500 chairs.</c>

36cfe60910854e03ad8f56bad6f91b51
00:44:05.000 --> 00:44:10.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The goal for each chair
is to find "the furniture's inner soul"–</c>

b47ff80fadc84ef0ba962df988011345
00:44:10.480 --> 00:44:14.840 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–a driving force
that overshadows everything else.</c>

a80af5e78de74c8a8f1276b1d4640a7a
00:44:16.520 --> 00:44:21.560 align:left position:22%
When I was 6–7 years old
I heard him say to a visitor–

02357256a3f54f05be140c880a3ef7fb
00:44:21.720 --> 00:44:24.960 align:left position:22%
–that the chairs were his children.

68f202403e67456791740325df210aac
00:44:25.120 --> 00:44:29.520 align:left position:22%
"That doesn't fit!"
Those were I and my sister.

7e7345d7ed444335a1e593db898d420e
00:44:29.680 --> 00:44:36.160 align:left position:22%
But that I have understood afterwards,
that so it was.

819ffc16603e4e68a7d75ff6da1627f7
00:44:55.200 --> 00:44:59.320 align:left position:22%
Better than all other designers.

6003cec0262f4a48b724a172c6f6f832
00:44:59.480 --> 00:45:05.120 align:left position:22%
For me it is about
his understanding of the materials.

b2b17019a95543a5baa5fe18a9310bec
00:45:05.280 --> 00:45:09.080 align:left position:22%
He never made anything that was impossible.

34d8a9cd610f4a469a14715710842f33
00:45:09.240 --> 00:45:14.280 align:left position:22%
He had thought through everything
from how the materials work.

624a2b9c010d4b6ea231ef5abd97905e
00:45:16.080 --> 00:45:21.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The wood's properties must go hand
in hand with the human body.</c>

b2883afdc94942c2917179ac091c1532
00:45:21.520 --> 00:45:24.040 align:left position:22%
A sitting person...

469b7123804347538d445140335f1e97
00:45:26.560 --> 00:45:30.400 align:left position:22%
Here is the back support, and it is important...

70d68df9a3dd4d4dad8b65a73ae724ed
00:45:30.560 --> 00:45:38.360 align:left position:22%
...that the back's internal curve feels...
the back support.

82cced8a0e94464e9ff609ad07f73c2a
00:45:38.520 --> 00:45:43.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>When Hans Wegner begins
as a carpenter apprentice at 14 years old–</c>

0f63165d9a7d49ed9add3455a821dd71
00:45:43.440 --> 00:45:46.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–he has no idea that his furniture craft–</c>

16afce56b59749ee8ee5d18b5d3a3178
00:45:46.400 --> 00:45:51.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–one day will be part of deciding
an American presidential election.</c>

bc546139dcf94fdb9588c4f2083d148f
00:45:51.720 --> 00:45:56.120 align:left position:22%
What senator Kennedy says
many of us can agree with.

aa846ad95fe44265b7873519c4bf70f2
00:45:56.280 --> 00:46:02.320 align:left position:22%
We can under no circumstances
discuss the United States' affairs.

630931ded0e44b028152187643a28f7d
00:46:02.480 --> 00:46:07.800 align:left position:22%
Kennedy looked so elegant
when he sat in this chair.

d370fb44fadc43699da253168d7cc945
00:46:07.960 --> 00:46:12.800 align:left position:22%
But Nixon looked like
a little schoolboy.

bae10561fe2740c6a8550a252e33a37b
00:46:12.960 --> 00:46:16.760 align:left position:22%
He didn't know where to put himself.

1400a5d537ff40ce9e1a992e3f740e64
00:46:16.920 --> 00:46:20.360 align:left position:22%
It might have had significance for the election.

4f334165c5114c87869d65d9cf59cd68
00:46:20.520 --> 00:46:27.680 align:left position:22%
It was not the chair's merit,
but it participated in a big event.

0be82ac3a805498aa847ba1ba6604638
00:46:27.840 --> 00:46:30.880 align:left position:22%
...under its worst attack so far.

2487363a1ba442ab80bc13fa1259b308
00:46:31.040 --> 00:46:37.000 align:left position:22%
My father was not one who bragged,
but we felt on his deathbed–

5b9f4aefd1394950a20dcdb143664457
00:46:37.160 --> 00:46:43.800 align:left position:22%
–that it was a great recognition
that it got to be on such a place.

3d736efb5bbd4c6eb8748ba28b6b22b2
00:46:43.960 --> 00:46:47.880 align:left position:22%
It was big,
for he became known abroad.

9e17f62e48894d9c836e24c62157bcfa
00:46:48.040 --> 00:46:53.600 align:left position:22%
Americans came to Denmark
to see what we were doing.

4fa1ee4c04f146b2b7dc247e1668f8c0
00:46:55.200 --> 00:47:01.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The chair becomes an icon for the organic
modernist furniture design–</c>

c4ec4b175312473395b60f32707f32d7
00:47:01.960 --> 00:47:05.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–but it is also a milestone
for Wegner himself.</c>

980a6a16490a454892ff91dbb0409473
00:47:09.120 --> 00:47:15.160 align:left position:22%
Yes, that chair is probably
Wegner's most important work.

0b84dcbc9806497685b4851c89da0982
00:47:15.320 --> 00:47:18.000 align:left position:22%
He found his own style.

7a6f6c3760e14440913d1c14483bc681
00:47:18.160 --> 00:47:21.680 align:left position:22%
Much of what he had done before–

3dffc1d9eb184941a253fd9c7e7515ef
00:47:21.840 --> 00:47:27.760 align:left position:22%
–was interpretations of other designers' works
or other cultures' design.

55aa4b17f4ca41aaaac2ffa992a73b5a
00:47:27.920 --> 00:47:33.280 align:left position:22%
But with that chair
he found his way to his own style.

babb6d49915e4566882c0dec08eab1d3
00:47:33.440 --> 00:47:37.080 align:left position:22%
What will your next chair look like?

56919f9028bf46ea8f15375e8d5b9fd7
00:47:37.240 --> 00:47:39.880 align:left position:22%
I don't know.

f32327b5642944b198d11e424930df81
00:47:40.680 --> 00:47:44.360 align:left position:22%
It can be anything.

1efbad2975d24eda9a07d63e18c5adbe
00:47:54.600 --> 00:47:59.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>When Poul and Inger Henningsen and
Arne and Jonna Jacobsen are in Denmark–</c>

44e9f9e476134a20ba983515575956b0
00:47:59.960 --> 00:48:03.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–they reunite with their families.</c>

b3edd503296348b1b8c3e4451a93303e
00:48:03.680 --> 00:48:10.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>The memories from the perilous flight over
the Øresund are still there for all.</c>

ae566500b73e4005bc8993afbaf620c7
00:48:10.440 --> 00:48:15.000 align:left position:22%
They didn't know
when they would come back.

3ecac1089a954d0a97cfd0645eb87889
00:48:15.160 --> 00:48:19.040 align:left position:22%
The children might not forgive–

a4e8d171dae14f6ab8eeb90a87a76a38
00:48:19.200 --> 00:48:24.560 align:left position:22%
–but they forgave their mother,
and the family reunited.

f4127ac97983412aa1c8cc682f15b7ef
00:48:24.720 --> 00:48:28.280 align:left position:22%
That I find fantastic.

d96c87bbea0a4d6ba67154771c2fd6c5
00:48:31.360 --> 00:48:35.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>In Copenhagen wants Arne Jacobsen to begin
a completely new chapter.</c>

380043e322de4907b891222351dfe561
00:48:36.040 --> 00:48:41.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>He is attracted by modern materials
and the industry that can mass produce.</c>

c46eedafa38841bb982217e5f60d1c43
00:48:41.640 --> 00:48:46.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>With molded plywood
he creates a light, stackable chair–</c>

db252378f1ff49648df0acee715347da
00:48:47.040 --> 00:48:49.440 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–with minimal material use–</c>

500852b37d294f0a9ad31bcc3a8cfb19
00:48:49.600 --> 00:48:55.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–that at first meets skepticism,
but soon is loved by a whole world.</c>

d247e425bdae4371aa9deab09d1e20f8
00:48:57.520 --> 00:49:01.840 align:left position:22%
The Ant has such a special form.

6860e4d336e54f8895b000cee4bac2cd
00:49:02.000 --> 00:49:05.280 align:left position:22%
The form you might think is just nice–

54d1646fa76c490bae14ce3d0a978bb2
00:49:05.440 --> 00:49:10.240 align:left position:22%
–but it is a prerequisite
for making the chair nimble.

cc658dd759b5466bbcbdd1aae29355dd
00:49:10.400 --> 00:49:15.200 align:left position:22%
It was a response to the post-war period,
everything should be modern.

cf50779df5704fcba746a3a0e7ca5233
00:49:15.360 --> 00:49:19.840 align:left position:22%
But had a completely different type
of industrialization.

532741cc41124236a783306e67a38ea8
00:49:20.000 --> 00:49:23.920 align:left position:22%
But wanted to leave the old Denmark
behind.

fb02702c71284f46b20acead57e72fa7
00:49:44.880 --> 00:49:48.360 align:left position:22%
If it is not nice to be natural...

f3f011bb89cd48f18658c37065c64de2
00:49:48.520 --> 00:49:51.040 align:left position:22%
...I don't want to be nice.

e9a561c5a6a14b41a967d538975f4852
00:49:54.480 --> 00:50:00.160 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Poul Henningsen who always wanted
to create a soft and pleasant light–</c>

5bdb2a16719b4938ba2a7cd86fecf39d
00:50:00.320 --> 00:50:06.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–gets problems during the post-war period,
when the light bulbs quickly develop.</c>

600a9ade8195465d93b10484bc144131
00:50:06.880 --> 00:50:10.880 align:left position:22%
Those who call themselves light technicians–

df48c4194799451a9f7b6805215e6e98
00:50:11.040 --> 00:50:16.960 align:left position:22%
–have never seriously
cared about the light's colors.

c453691542e741f7a99a8c4d19fc2eea
00:50:22.640 --> 00:50:26.720 align:left position:22%
It is they
who give life and light its richness.

744604290485422cba87f39726a43a90
00:50:28.840 --> 00:50:32.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Now no longer suffice
his three-shaded lamps–</c>

5dd83c8dbcce461e8d7e7f42bac8d872
00:50:32.400 --> 00:50:37.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–that made such success
at the Paris exhibition 1925.</c>

1e00957487f644988ba322e951696e8f
00:50:37.880 --> 00:50:44.360 align:left position:22%
What Poul Henningsen does is a lamp
that completely encloses the light.

cba0693afb88470f9699d80b102ffc8a
00:50:44.520 --> 00:50:49.760 align:left position:22%
He makes namely the very, very
famous PH5 lamp.

d76150d7e4a54081a6c4265d42e27007
00:50:51.000 --> 00:50:54.520 align:left position:22%
It has four reflective screens–

1eb8ff6e0c734dda8a7409ae0f4f4e26
00:50:54.680 --> 00:51:01.880 align:left position:22%
–but it also has screens inside that
make the light warm and a bit red.

9ba92245b74940ea9b466f943059cf2d
00:51:02.040 --> 00:51:06.440 align:left position:22%
It begins to be produced
when Denmark has high prosperity.

32548aba5ad54a68b538db2c6dbb02f0
00:51:06.600 --> 00:51:11.200 align:left position:22%
Soon there is a PH5 lamp
in every fifth Danish home.

ad12e7defcc9441f91a92141d8edac31
00:51:12.560 --> 00:51:18.920 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Poul Henningsen also creates the
glare-free but complex lamp Artichoke–</c>

0262f2a9fec140d0b752ff01fd09c854
00:51:19.080 --> 00:51:23.240 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–or the Thistle
as it is also called.</c>

3b3c42d37d284f6d92dcc83a9f1ca116
00:51:29.000 --> 00:51:35.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>In the time and in sync with prosperity
lies that one travels on charter trips.</c>

1e0bf0b0870949fba0cfa67ac241e81f
00:51:35.960 --> 00:51:43.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It is now Arne Jacobsen erects
his foremost work, SAS Royal Hotel–</c>

a6adda0fb8c548e8951e27da56d992fc
00:51:43.640 --> 00:51:46.880 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–an airport terminal with hotel–</c>

c44803c748de41eba5342f30d66c6b79
00:51:47.040 --> 00:51:51.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and Denmark's first skyscraper,
right in Copenhagen.</c>

e7549361c08643d0b418e349c1a9f7f3
00:51:52.040 --> 00:51:57.600 align:left position:22%
For Jacobsen was it an all-artwork
and everything fits together – big and small.

823919f2fe5c482d943ea33245993578
00:51:57.760 --> 00:52:04.360 align:left position:22%
He did the layout,
the color scheme and the textiles.

c63c6803fc8c42b18aa749386c8cb819
00:52:04.520 --> 00:52:09.800 align:left position:22%
He designed
the furniture, the door handles... Everything.

198302a90ba143f087adac0bd6ee4476
00:52:17.400 --> 00:52:21.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And the for the hotel specially made,
futuristic cutlery–</c>

861a9e07aad84985a01138cfd2eaacfc
00:52:21.680 --> 00:52:26.280 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–with erased boundary between
handle and blade become film history.</c>

e5860b14e4fd41b9a88d56d8e63c33f8
00:52:27.600 --> 00:52:33.120 align:left position:22%
–How is it going?
–Fantastic. We have nothing to complain about.

5a5605395e5a494b81bfdc797c305d0c
00:52:34.360 --> 00:52:40.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And probably the most talked about cutlery
that has ever been shown on the big screen.</c>

76beee3a7fd644fbb61f2fee9d266a6b
00:52:51.800 --> 00:52:57.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>When Danish design is at its greatest
it gets a new life in Iceland.</c>

405d8f22c1e240449f6db7ec7f39e722
00:53:00.640 --> 00:53:06.640 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>It is when Icelandic Halldor
Hjálmarsson goes to Denmark–</c>

e51c8120367d43779251e439dafb33a0
00:53:06.800 --> 00:53:10.440 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–to study
at the School of Arts and Crafts.</c>

8aa86bee91bf49eb8186f03bc298bf4f
00:53:13.240 --> 00:53:18.040 align:left position:22%
He had the luck to be there
just when Danish design...

39921c09caf3449db10a38ba03401ac5
00:53:18.200 --> 00:53:23.120 align:left position:22%
...was growing. And became world-famous.

b6a9454bbb854de5a35dce2c01c1ef2c
00:53:23.280 --> 00:53:27.400 align:left position:22%
His teachers were the time's
most prominent designers.

58f8bc2373ff435facb4bb6f282e749a
00:53:27.560 --> 00:53:32.480 align:left position:22%
Poul Kjærholm
was his main teacher–

4c8ccfd9d52146328a82dbf9a9e1e28a
00:53:32.640 --> 00:53:35.240 align:left position:22%
–and his supervisor and friend.

64a9989ef0914ab9bbb12b17a7d5ed10
00:53:37.240 --> 00:53:41.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Danish designer Poul Kjærholm,
carpenter by trade–</c>

de99dba5d3b8496588b5ec83cced33fb
00:53:41.640 --> 00:53:44.080 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–often chooses to leave wood as material.</c>

048e7d8b5a9b4cf3b93f4be2bffdd25f
00:53:44.240 --> 00:53:48.480 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>He is modern and prefers to create
in steel and leather–</c>

e9cea0f2bb3b45f7869d9031b10946af
00:53:48.640 --> 00:53:52.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–something that makes impression
on Halldor Hjálmarsson.</c>

e1c5b58a99ea4f50a1e10a3129a2f987
00:53:52.560 --> 00:53:55.560 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>He also lets himself be inspired
by Arne Jacobsen–</c>

59ce9e3717f64f66bd9601b9cae8877d
00:53:55.720 --> 00:54:00.200 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–and decides to make
an Icelandic and more stable version–</c>

ac5f9d87a8c445c39a6e9a9c580147ae
00:54:00.360 --> 00:54:02.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–of the success chair Ant.</c>

00b6ef9a7d2d41d09a41236e8a951428
00:54:05.560 --> 00:54:10.000 align:left position:22%
The model is the Danish Ant
that came 1953.

34a596d85e0c4a818a7b3d5c9f2a8cff
00:54:11.840 --> 00:54:16.240 align:left position:22%
But a problem was
that the back went broken.

1715271dcf72414db0f111784e86d67b
00:54:16.400 --> 00:54:20.600 align:left position:22%
It had only three legs,
and the attachments were quite complicated.

d440ee8fe2814810a9341db1efac59d3
00:54:20.760 --> 00:54:25.000 align:left position:22%
With that as starting point
he begins to think–

e464d0e343e6456e81090a73c04880f2
00:54:25.160 --> 00:54:28.800 align:left position:22%
–and the result becomes the chair Skata.

53302137b4504d55bd6c02c8be460be5
00:54:29.760 --> 00:54:34.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>With Halldor Hjálmarsson comes the
modern material and form–</c>

0095340b83694bf1ba10f9021188e9cb
00:54:34.200 --> 00:54:39.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–to the traditional Iceland,
but now with a whiff of the Atlantic.</c>

1405e3cfdb8448999657ab7d75e2ae7b
00:54:53.080 --> 00:54:57.840 align:left position:22%
The thought behind the chair is poetic,
the form is inspired by the fish rockfish.

db788ccabed2400195517ca660c6879d
00:54:59.240 --> 00:55:04.480 align:left position:22%
And the attachments he develops
to simplify assembly–

8a44c1c13cd44ffcbba02bd16b3389d7
00:55:04.640 --> 00:55:07.720 align:left position:22%
–are an allusion to the rockfish's eggs.

b3247fb1bbd14e90ac92e82f67220cf7
00:55:07.880 --> 00:55:13.360 align:left position:22%
It lays four eggs in an egg capsule,
"mermaid's purse" in English.

b3e0aa69b51547be81bcc960392bedcd
00:55:13.520 --> 00:55:17.080 align:left position:22%
So the chair is in a way a sculpture.

3f6f14872e1a4df78880df7f7acc7697
00:55:19.160 --> 00:55:24.360 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>With Halldor Hjálmarsson becomes the
Danish ant to an Icelandic rockfish.</c>

c65b260efc42428e9df261fb4ce91890
00:55:24.520 --> 00:55:29.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And when the designer gets commissioned
to furnish Reykjavik's first café–</c>

8014289950fb416b965489b43ae753a9
00:55:29.880 --> 00:55:35.720 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–he does it as a tribute
to his old teacher in Denmark.</c>

7545f3a8067243a29e35c9a9970f334d
00:55:40.680 --> 00:55:46.120 align:left position:22%
He designed the whole place,
both the layout–

32552004fa3b40a3bd8e7b609a37046c
00:55:46.280 --> 00:55:50.440 align:left position:22%
–and also the furniture,
which is specially made for the café.

4b2d90f22c684cffaedb99700ea49794
00:55:50.600 --> 00:55:56.800 align:left position:22%
The furniture is inspired by Kjærholm,
he uses a lot of flat iron.

26aa27f1673e47b19256ee3b61de57ed
00:56:09.200 --> 00:56:14.320 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>Poul Henningsen and Arne Jacobsen's
perilous flight over the Øresund–</c>

04ded7ade1b74670b2aa06555127f23d
00:56:14.480 --> 00:56:17.400 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–probably saved their lives–</c>

c5a9a44487aa4938b7ce2df8afa7ff27
00:56:17.560 --> 00:56:22.040 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–but it is the design
that has made them immortal.</c>

dde361067db6493f8d4175704960289c
00:56:24.320 --> 00:56:28.440 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>And perhaps it is so
with all carefully made things–</c>

742090c7cff1456cb82e9b06f16ddc
00:56:28.600 --> 00:56:30.800 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–that they outlive us.</c>

c1f9d6635189425ca1eb79798b1fe5a3
00:56:33.400 --> 00:56:36.000 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>In Higashikawa in Hokkaido, Japan–</c>

6bd284a91ba8496da43888e3bb32ac0f
00:56:36.160 --> 00:56:40.520 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–prepares Mr. Oda to hand over his life's work.</c>

dbe47684695f4d688e32a86359c60fd8
00:56:40.680 --> 00:56:45.600 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>His dream is that the Nordic furniture
he has collected during his life–</c>

e904c224768e432d929888a44dc36e24
00:56:45.760 --> 00:56:49.760 align:left position:22%
<c.teletext>–one day will become
its own design museum.</c>

7e991a1489da46399cc2e3d49cf4d026
00:56:52.280 --> 00:56:58.600 align:left position:22%
I am going to move away from here
some time to spring next year.

2ad1285209b74e29bea9647fcfbd1551
00:56:59.920 --> 00:57:05.160 align:left position:22%
And I can not
take the furniture to heaven.

d1b36985d8b34a78aedd1590d0960c7a
00:57:09.400 --> 00:57:16.200 align:left position:22%
With everything that I have done
and collected for my research–

1e135662b83346d9992531b58e7a23cf
00:57:16.360 --> 00:57:22.880 align:left position:22%
–I want to give young people opportunity
to see solid objects and discover–

1ed61cdb5ff944f79a442e33a12e55bb
00:57:23.040 --> 00:57:26.880 align:left position:22%
–that there is
something else than wear and tear.

a2927f34ee18485486cba84301b8e7f8
00:57:27.040 --> 00:57:31.560 align:left position:22%
This is furniture
with very long lifespan.

330cc942b3ca45738ebfab756653dcea
00:57:31.720 --> 00:57:37.160 align:left position:22%
One can see the roots.
Such a design museum I want to open.

afbc29943a54413a900eb09413be89b3
00:57:37.320 --> 00:57:44.080 align:left position:22%
I want that young people
should understand craftsmanship of really high quality.

4732e8870ec949439203622708831026
00:57:44.240 --> 00:57:49.200 align:left position:22%
On such a design museum
one could see the authentic originals.

fc748e812e4b413db77d1abea382adf8
00:57:54.200 --> 00:57:58.120 align:left position:22%
I have always been fascinated by the 60s.

4e99090b229d411e8a0fa7f71cc1bb21
00:58:00.360 --> 00:58:04.400 align:left position:22%
In this film
we will talk about plastics.

94c1a27503014d1094ceec95f5d8de9a
00:58:06.760 --> 00:58:12.440 align:left position:22%
The magical year 2000 is approaching.
How will we live? What will we do?

8edfaf222d364b3aac44650229ed845e
00:58:12.600 --> 00:58:15.640 align:left position:22%
<c.urfjarran><i>Ignition sequence initiated. Five...</i></c>

06f382a8def34f91968864067fc89f64
00:58:15.800 --> 00:58:20.080 align:left position:22%
All colorful things
make me just so happy.

